list.abstract: Entrance（英 [ˈentrəns , ɪnˈtrɑːns]，美 [ˈentrəns , ɪnˈtræns]），英语单词，作名词用，为入口；进口；门口。作动词用，为使狂喜；使着迷；使出神。短语搭配有entrance examination（入学考试），例句为“The red painted pillars of the entrance gate.（入口大门的红漆柱子。）” Entrance名词类近义词有threshold、access、portal等。entry强调正式地、礼仪地进入；用作“入口”解时，多指房门、院门、门廊等。entrance含义广泛，作“进入”解时，可用于许多场合；作“入口”解时，指有门或栏的入口处。

yingyinNormal.en: What do you want from me? The maze. How do I find the entrance?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你到底想干什么？那个迷宫，我要怎么找到入口？

yingyinNormal.en: It's a corner spot, cutting the risk of door-dings in half. It's a mere 28 steps from the building entrance.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那车位是在角落，车门被旁车门撞凹的机率少了一半，而走到楼入口处也只需仅仅28步。

yingyinNormal.en: And I had tried to get in the gym, And they stopped me. And they were like, "oh, sorry, this is the players' entrance." I was like, "I know."
yingyinNormal.zh: 当我试图进入球馆时 他们拦住我，他们说“抱歉，这里是球员入口” 我说，“我知道啊”

yingyinNormal.en: You guys, never underestimate the power of a dramatic entrance.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大伙儿，永远不要低估华丽出场的威力。

yingyinNormal.en: Whoa ,nice dramatic entrance. What's the occasion? Today will be my final class.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哇，好华丽的出场，今天是什么日子呀？今天将是我的最后一堂课。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm sorry, if you didn't cheer at my entrance, it's too late to buy into the premise.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不好意思，如果你没有为我的出场欢呼，那你现在提出你的假设也为时已晚了。

yingyinNormal.en: Holy shit! You want to open a window? I was trying to give you an entrance. Thank you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的天！你要开个窗吗？我在给你腾个地方。谢谢你了。

yingyinNormal.en: Before the battle of the fist comes the battle of the mind. Hence, the dramatic entrance.
yingyinNormal.zh: 双方交战先比气势，后比拳头，因此，出场就是要华丽。

yingyinNormal.en: God save the Queen! She could open a slaughterhouse and we'd all probably pay the entrance fee.
yingyinNormal.zh: 天佑女王！她可以建一座屠宰场而我们可能还得花钱买票入场。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, yes Ross, pressing my third nipple opens the delivery entrance to the magical land of Narnia.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只要压我的第三个乳头，就会开启纳尼亚王国（著名的儿童魔幻小说）之门。

yingyinNormal.en: Dramatic entrance? Master Shifu. The Dragon Warrior is correct. Really? I was just making.... yeah, I mean, yeah, I am.
yingyinNormal.zh: 华丽出场？师傅。神龙大侠说得对。是吗？我只是随口...啊，对，我就这个意思。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, I have my own wholesale flower business and I want to hook up my computer in the front entrance with the one in my refrigerated warehouse.
yingyinNormal.zh: 太好了，我个人在开展鲜花批发业务，我想把我的前台计算机和冷藏库的计算机连在一起。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

derivative_info_list.mean: n. 入口；进口；门口；门；进入；上场；登台；涉足；开始进入；进入某地（或加入某组织）的权利

examination_example.sentence_trans: 旅游方案A——巴斯和巨石阵，包括古罗马浴室和巨石阵的入场门票。

sense_info_list.en: the right, means, or opportunity to enter somewhere or be a member of an institution, society, or other body

examination_example.sentence: The gap year phenomenon originated (起源) with the months left over to Oxbridge applicants between <highlight>entrance</highlight> exams and the next academic year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 间隔年现象起源于牛津和剑桥申请者在1入学考试和下一学年之间的几个月的空档期。

examination_example.sentence: Rome's Colosseum was 157 feet tall and had 80 <highlight>entrances</highlight>, seating 50,000 people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 罗马斗兽场高157英尺，有80个入口，可容纳5万人。

examination_example.sentence: Pushchairs and wheelchairs are available to rent at the Information Desk and Denny Way <highlight>entrance</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在问询处和丹尼路入口处有折叠式婴儿车和轮椅可供租用。
